[Birds tweeting]

489
00:27:20,436 --> 00:27:22,461
They never want me
to meet anyone.

490
00:27:25,608 --> 00:27:27,303
[Giggles]

491
00:27:27,343 --> 00:27:29,470
But you know something?

492
00:27:29,512 --> 00:27:31,980
Whispering]
l fooled them.

493
00:27:32,014 --> 00:27:34,710
l have met someone.

494
00:27:34,750 --> 00:27:35,876
Whoo!

495
00:27:38,954 --> 00:27:40,854
Whoo! Whoo!

496
00:27:42,057 --> 00:27:45,049
Oh...a Prince.

497
00:27:45,094 --> 00:27:46,721
[Tweeting]

498
00:27:46,762 --> 00:27:51,199
Well, he's tall
and handsome and...

499
00:27:51,233 --> 00:27:53,326
and so romantic!

500
00:27:53,369 --> 00:27:55,667
[Tweeting]

501
00:27:55,704 --> 00:28:00,801
Oh, we walk together
and talk together...

502
00:28:00,843 --> 00:28:03,903
and just before
we say good-bye...

503
00:28:03,946 --> 00:28:06,005
he takes me in his arms...

504
00:28:06,048 --> 00:28:07,037
[Tweeting]

505
00:28:07,082 --> 00:28:08,310
And then...

506
00:28:08,350 --> 00:28:10,113
[Tweeting loudly]

507
00:28:10,152 --> 00:28:11,346
l wake up.

508
00:28:11,387 --> 00:28:13,685
[Sighing tweet]

509
00:28:15,291 --> 00:28:19,159
<i>BRIAR ROSE: Yes,</i>
<i>it's only in my dreams.</i>

510
00:28:19,195 --> 00:28:21,595
<i>But they say if you dream</i>
<i>a thing more than once...</i>

511
00:28:21,630 --> 00:28:23,860
it's sure to come true.

512
00:28:23,899 --> 00:28:27,198
And I've seen him
so many times.

513
00:28:28,470 --> 00:28:30,461
<i>[Briar Rose humming]</i>

514
00:28:49,792 --> 00:28:52,454
[Chuckling]

515
00:28:56,298 --> 00:28:57,492
[Tweeting]

516
00:29:06,809 --> 00:29:08,504
[Tweeting]

517
00:29:08,544 --> 00:29:11,240
<i>MAN: You know, Samson...</i>

518
00:29:11,280 --> 00:29:15,011
there's something strange
about that voice.

519
00:29:15,050 --> 00:29:16,984
Too beautiful to be real.

520
00:29:18,287 --> 00:29:21,017
<i>MAN: Maybe it was</i>
<i>some mysterious being...</i>

521
00:29:21,056 --> 00:29:22,921
a...a wood sprite or a...

522
00:29:22,958 --> 00:29:24,016
[Snorts]

523
00:29:24,059 --> 00:29:25,583
[Neighs]

524
00:29:25,628 --> 00:29:27,357
<i>MAN: Here! Stop!</i>

525
00:29:32,334 --> 00:29:33,961
[Birds tweeting]

526
00:29:50,319 --> 00:29:54,085
[Birds tweet
and Briar Rose hums]

527
00:29:54,123 --> 00:29:55,852
<i>[Owl chuckles]</i>

528
00:29:55,891 --> 00:29:57,256
[Gasps]

529
00:29:57,293 --> 00:30:00,729
<i>BRIAR ROSE: Why,</i>
<i>it's my dream Prince!</i>

530
00:30:00,763 --> 00:30:04,062
<i>[Briar Rose giggles]</i>

531
00:30:04,099 --> 00:30:06,567
Your Highness.

532
00:30:06,602 --> 00:30:08,502
[Sings]

533
00:30:12,041 --> 00:30:14,032
You know, I'm really
not supposed...

534
00:30:14,076 --> 00:30:15,771
to speak to strangers...

535
00:30:15,811 --> 00:30:17,745
but we've met before.

536
00:30:17,780 --> 00:30:20,977
<i>I know you</i>

537
00:30:21,016 --> 00:30:26,545
<i>I waked with you</i>
<i>once upon a dream</i>

538
00:30:26,588 --> 00:30:29,113
<i>I know you</i>

539
00:30:29,158 --> 00:30:34,755
<i>The gleam in your eyes</i>
<i>is so familiar a gleam</i>

540
00:30:34,797 --> 00:30:38,563
<i>And I know it's true</i>

541
00:30:38,600 --> 00:30:43,264
<i>That visions are seldom</i>
<i>all they seem</i>

542
00:30:43,305 --> 00:30:46,001
<i>But if I know you</i>

543
00:30:46,041 --> 00:30:48,475
<i>I know what you'll do</i>

544
00:30:48,510 --> 00:30:51,741
<i>You'll Love me at once</i>

545
00:30:51,780 --> 00:31:00,245
<i>The way you did once</i>
<i>upon a dream</i>

546
00:31:00,289 --> 00:31:02,120
[Sings]

547
00:31:07,963 --> 00:31:10,329
<i>But if I know you</i>

548
00:31:10,366 --> 00:31:13,062
<i>I know what you'll do</i>

549
00:31:13,102 --> 00:31:16,503
<i>You'll Love me at once</i>

550
00:31:16,538 --> 00:31:22,966
<i>MAN: The way you did</i>
<i>once upon a dream</i>

551
00:31:23,011 --> 00:31:25,912
[Chuckles]
BRIAR ROSE: Oh!

552
00:31:25,948 --> 00:31:27,142
Oh!

553
00:31:27,182 --> 00:31:28,513
I'm awfully sorry.

554
00:31:28,550 --> 00:31:30,711
l didn't mean to frighten you.

555
00:31:30,753 --> 00:31:33,187
Oh, it...wasn't that.

556
00:31:33,222 --> 00:31:35,952
It's just that
you're a...a...

557
00:31:35,991 --> 00:31:37,424
A stranger?

558
00:31:37,459 --> 00:31:38,483
<i>BRIAR ROSE: Mm-hmm.</i>

559
00:31:38,527 --> 00:31:39,619
<i>MAN: But don't you remember?</i>

560
00:31:39,661 --> 00:31:41,128
<i>We've met before.</i>

561
00:31:41,163 --> 00:31:42,255
We--we have?

562
00:31:42,297 --> 00:31:43,286
Well, of course.

563
00:31:43,332 --> 00:31:44,526
You said so yourself.

564
00:31:44,566 --> 00:31:46,761
''Once upon a dream.''

565
00:31:46,802 --> 00:31:49,236
<i>MAN: I know you</i>

566
00:31:49,271 --> 00:31:54,766
<i>I walked with you</i>
<i>once upon a dream</i>

567
00:31:54,810 --> 00:31:57,973
<i>I know you</i>

568
00:31:58,013 --> 00:32:00,038
<i>The gleam in your eyes</i>

569
00:32:00,082 --> 00:32:03,950
<i>Is so familiar a gleam</i>

570
00:32:03,986 --> 00:32:10,516
<i>CHOIR:</i>
<i>And I know it's true</i>

571
00:32:10,559 --> 00:32:15,997
<i>That visions are</i>
<i>seldom all they seem</i>

572
00:32:16,031 --> 00:32:19,967
<i>But if I know you</i>

573
00:32:20,002 --> 00:32:22,903
<i>I know what you'll do</i>

574
00:32:22,938 --> 00:32:26,135
<i>You'll Love me at once</i>

575
00:32:26,175 --> 00:32:29,906
<i>The way you did once</i>

576
00:32:29,945 --> 00:32:38,944
<i>Upon a dream</i>

577
00:32:43,459 --> 00:32:45,154
Who are you?

578
00:32:45,194 --> 00:32:46,627
What's your name?

579
00:32:47,796 --> 00:32:48,922
Hmm?

580
00:32:50,232 --> 00:32:52,257
Oh. My name.

581
00:32:52,301 --> 00:32:54,030
Why, it's...

582
00:32:54,069 --> 00:32:55,502
it's...

583
00:32:55,537 --> 00:32:56,868
Oh, no, no! l can't! l--

584
00:32:58,540 --> 00:32:59,507
Good-bye!

585
00:32:59,541 --> 00:33:00,803
But when will l see you again?

586
00:33:00,843 --> 00:33:02,708
Oh, never! Never!

587
00:33:02,744 --> 00:33:04,507
<i>MAN: Never!</i>

588
00:33:04,546 --> 00:33:07,014
Well...maybe someday.

589
00:33:07,049 --> 00:33:08,482
When? Tomorrow?

590
00:33:08,517 --> 00:33:11,247
<i>BRIAR ROSE:</i>
<i>Oh, no. This evening.</i>

591
00:33:11,286 --> 00:33:12,344
<i>MAN: Where?</i>

592
00:33:12,387 --> 00:33:14,787
At the cottage, in the glen.

593
00:33:20,028 --> 00:33:22,462
<i>[Fauna humming]</i>

594
00:33:22,498 --> 00:33:23,465
<i>[Blows out match]</i>

595
00:33:23,499 --> 00:33:24,693
There.

596
00:33:24,733 --> 00:33:25,995
Whoop!

597
00:33:31,473 --> 00:33:33,304
Well, what do you think of it?

598
00:33:33,342 --> 00:33:34,969
Why, it--

599
00:33:35,010 --> 00:33:37,945
it's a very unusual
cake, isn't it?

600
00:33:37,980 --> 00:33:39,709
Yes.

601
00:33:39,748 --> 00:33:42,546
Of course, it will be
much stiffer after it's baked.

602
00:33:42,584 --> 00:33:44,051
<i>FLORA: Of course, dear.</i>

603
00:33:44,086 --> 00:33:46,577
Um...what do you
think of the dress?

604
00:33:46,622 --> 00:33:48,556
Well, it--it's...

605
00:33:48,590 --> 00:33:50,455
<i>FAUNA: It-it's not exactly...</i>

606
00:33:50,492 --> 00:33:52,221
<i>the way it is in</i>
<i>the book, is it?</i>

607
00:33:52,261 --> 00:33:54,161
Oh, l improved it.

608
00:33:54,196 --> 00:33:57,029
But perhaps if l added
a few more ruffles...

609
00:33:57,065 --> 00:33:59,124
uh, what do you think?

610
00:33:59,167 --> 00:34:02,068
Um...l think so.

611
00:34:02,104 --> 00:34:03,696
What do you think,
Merryweather?

612
00:34:03,739 --> 00:34:07,766
l think we've had enough
of this nonsense!

613
00:34:07,809 --> 00:34:09,640
l think we ought
to think of Rose

614
00:34:09,678 --> 00:34:12,772
and what she'll
think of this mess!

615
00:34:12,814 --> 00:34:15,442
l still think what
l thunk before.

616
00:34:15,484 --> 00:34:17,509
<i>I'm going to get those wands!</i>

617
00:34:19,821 --> 00:34:22,654
You know...l think
she's right.

618
00:34:23,825 --> 00:34:26,225
Here they are!
Good as new!

619
00:34:26,261 --> 00:34:27,592
<i>FLORA: Uh, uh, tut,</i>
<i>tut, tut, tut--</i>

620
00:34:27,629 --> 00:34:30,427
C-c-careful, Merryweather.

621
00:34:30,465 --> 00:34:31,454
[Quietly]
Quick!

622
00:34:31,500 --> 00:34:33,593
Lock the doors.

623
00:34:33,635 --> 00:34:35,398
<i>FLORA: Fauna,</i>
<i>you close the windows.</i>

624
00:34:35,437 --> 00:34:38,406
<i>Oh, plug up every cranny.</i>

625
00:34:38,440 --> 00:34:40,408
We can't take any chances.

626
00:34:40,442 --> 00:34:41,909
[Door squeaks]

627
00:34:41,944 --> 00:34:44,469
Now, you take care
of the cake.

628
00:34:44,513 --> 00:34:45,480
<i>MERRYWEATHER: While I--</i>

629
00:34:45,514 --> 00:34:46,947
Clean the room, dear.

630
00:34:46,982 --> 00:34:49,644
And I'll make the dress.

631
00:34:49,685 --> 00:34:50,652
<i>FAUNA: Now, hurry!</i>

632
00:34:50,686 --> 00:34:51,778
Ooh!

633
00:34:53,922 --> 00:34:56,083
Come on,
bucket, mop, broom.

634
00:34:56,124 --> 00:34:58,922
<i>Flora says,</i>
<i>''Clean up the room.''</i>

635
00:35:06,468 --> 00:35:08,026
<i>[Merryweather chuckling]</i>

636
00:35:08,070 --> 00:35:10,470
And now, to make a lovely dress

637
00:35:10,505 --> 00:35:12,803
fit to grace a fair Princess.

638
00:35:15,110 --> 00:35:17,203
<i>FAUNA: Eggs, flour, lemon</i>

639
00:35:17,245 --> 00:35:18,371
<i>[Voice cracks]</i>

640
00:35:18,413 --> 00:35:20,881
Just do it like it
says here in the book.

641
00:35:20,916 --> 00:35:22,816
I'll put on the candles.

642
00:35:51,046 --> 00:35:52,707
[Snipping]

643
00:36:16,938 --> 00:36:17,039
Oh, no! Not pink!

644
00:36:17,039 --> 00:36:19,007
Oh, no! Not pink!

645
00:36:19,041 --> 00:36:20,508
Make it blue!

646
00:36:20,542 --> 00:36:21,839
[Gasps]

647
00:36:21,877 --> 00:36:23,504
Merryweather!

648
00:36:23,545 --> 00:36:24,637
Make it pink.

649
00:36:28,583 --> 00:36:29,743
Whispering]
Make it blue.

650
00:36:31,953 --> 00:36:34,114
Oh! Pink!

651
00:36:35,991 --> 00:36:37,083
Blue!

652
00:37:03,285 --> 00:37:04,843
[Caws]

653
00:37:04,886 --> 00:37:06,444
[Cawing]

654
00:37:14,229 --> 00:37:15,594
[Caw caw]

655
00:37:29,644 --> 00:37:33,273
<i>FLORA: Oh, now look</i>
<i>what you've done!</i>

656
00:37:33,315 --> 00:37:34,282
<i>[Briar Rose singing distantly]</i>

657
00:37:34,316 --> 00:37:36,716
Shh! Shh! Listen!

658
00:37:36,752 --> 00:37:38,185
It's Rose!

659
00:37:38,220 --> 00:37:39,619
She's back!

660
00:37:39,654 --> 00:37:41,019
Enough of this foolishness!

661
00:37:44,826 --> 00:37:45,918
Make it pink.

662
00:37:45,961 --> 00:37:47,724
Now hide! Quick!

663
00:37:48,830 --> 00:37:50,593
<i>[Briar Rose singing distantly]</i>

664
00:37:50,632 --> 00:37:52,259
Whispering]
Blue!

665
00:37:52,300 --> 00:37:53,961
Aunt Flora!

666
00:37:56,037 --> 00:37:57,834
Good gracious!

667
00:37:57,873 --> 00:38:00,103
<i>Who left the mop running?</i>

668
00:38:00,142 --> 00:38:02,474
[Gasping]
Stop, mop!

669
00:38:05,080 --> 00:38:06,342
Aunt Flora!

670
00:38:06,381 --> 00:38:08,872
Fauna! Merryweather!

671
00:38:11,953 --> 00:38:13,443
<i>BRIAR ROSE:</i>
<i>Where is everybody?</i>

672
00:38:13,488 --> 00:38:14,455
[Gasps]

673
00:38:14,489 --> 00:38:16,150
Oh!

674
00:38:16,191 --> 00:38:18,284
<i>FAIRIES: Surprise! Surprise!</i>

675
00:38:18,326 --> 00:38:20,317
Happy Birthday!

676
00:38:20,362 --> 00:38:21,761
Oh, you darlings!

677
00:38:21,797 --> 00:38:24,664
This is the happiest day
of my life!

678
00:38:24,699 --> 00:38:27,167
Everything's so wonderful!

679
00:38:27,202 --> 00:38:29,033
Just wait till you meet him!

680
00:38:29,070 --> 00:38:30,298
Him?

681
00:38:30,338 --> 00:38:31,703
Rose!

682
00:38:31,740 --> 00:38:33,833
You've met some stranger?

683
00:38:33,875 --> 00:38:36,275
Oh, he's not a stranger.

684
00:38:36,311 --> 00:38:37,938
We've met before.

685
00:38:37,979 --> 00:38:38,946
You have?

686
00:38:38,980 --> 00:38:40,106
Where?

687
00:38:40,148 --> 00:38:42,343
Once upon a dream.

688
00:38:42,384 --> 00:38:45,012
<i>I know you</i>

689
00:38:45,053 --> 00:38:50,719
<i>I walked with you</i>
<i>once upon a dream</i>

690
00:38:50,759 --> 00:38:52,522
FAUNA: She's in love!

691
00:38:52,561 --> 00:38:55,359
-Oh, no!
-This is terrible!

692
00:38:55,397 --> 00:38:57,262
Why?

693
00:38:57,299 --> 00:38:58,857
After all, l am sixteen.

694
00:38:58,900 --> 00:39:00,959
it isn't that, dear.

695
00:39:01,002 --> 00:39:03,027
You're already betrothed.

696
00:39:03,071 --> 00:39:04,163
Betrothed?

697
00:39:04,206 --> 00:39:05,901
Since the day you were born.

698
00:39:05,941 --> 00:39:07,875
To Prince Phillip, dear.

699
00:39:07,909 --> 00:39:10,036
But that's impossible.

700
00:39:10,078 --> 00:39:11,739
How could l marry a Prince?

701
00:39:11,780 --> 00:39:13,008
<i>BRIAR ROSE:</i>
<i>I'd have to be--</i>

702
00:39:13,048 --> 00:39:14,072
A Princess.

703
00:39:14,115 --> 00:39:15,446
And you are, dear.

704
00:39:15,483 --> 00:39:17,007
Princess Aurora.

705
00:39:17,052 --> 00:39:21,648
<i>Tonight, we're taking you back</i>
<i>to your father, King Stefan.</i>

706
00:39:21,690 --> 00:39:24,124
But...but l can't!

707
00:39:24,159 --> 00:39:25,888
He's coming here tonight.

708
00:39:25,927 --> 00:39:27,189
<i>I promised to meet him.</i>

709
00:39:27,229 --> 00:39:28,719
<i>FLORA:</i>
<i>I'm sorry, child.</i>

710
00:39:28,763 --> 00:39:32,859
But you must never see
that young man again.

711
00:39:32,901 --> 00:39:34,994
Oh, no! No!

712
00:39:35,036 --> 00:39:37,334
<i>I can't believe it!</i>

713
00:39:37,372 --> 00:39:40,273
[Sobbing]
No! No!

714
00:39:44,946 --> 00:39:48,006
And we thought
she'd be so happy.

715
00:39:48,050 --> 00:39:49,984
[Sobbing]

716
00:40:00,996 --> 00:40:03,021
[Sighs]

717
00:40:03,065 --> 00:40:05,033
No sign of her yet, Hubert.

718
00:40:05,067 --> 00:40:08,002
[Munching]
Of course not.

719
00:40:08,036 --> 00:40:10,231
It's a good half-hour
till sunset.

720
00:40:12,374 --> 00:40:14,433
[Gulps and burps]

721
00:40:14,476 --> 00:40:16,103
Ah, excellent bird.

722
00:40:16,144 --> 00:40:18,408
Mmm!

723
00:40:18,447 --> 00:40:20,938
Aw, now, come, man!

724
00:40:20,982 --> 00:40:22,176
Buck up!

725
00:40:22,217 --> 00:40:23,775
Battle's over.

726
00:40:23,819 --> 00:40:25,719
<i>HUBERT: Girl is</i>
<i>as good as here.</i>

727
00:40:25,754 --> 00:40:27,085
I'm sorry, Hubert...

728
00:40:27,122 --> 00:40:30,182
but after sixteen years
of worrying...

729
00:40:30,225 --> 00:40:31,487
never knowing--

730
00:40:31,526 --> 00:40:34,393
The past! All in the past!

731
00:40:34,429 --> 00:40:36,863
[Claps]

732
00:40:40,235 --> 00:40:44,433
<i>HUBERT: Tonight,</i>
<i>we toast the future...</i>

733
00:40:44,473 --> 00:40:46,805
with something I've
been saving for sixteen years.

734
00:40:46,842 --> 00:40:48,537
[Chuckles]

735
00:40:50,278 --> 00:40:51,768
Here!

736
00:40:51,813 --> 00:40:53,110
To the future!

737
00:40:53,148 --> 00:40:54,445
<i>STEFAN: Right, Hubert.</i>

738
00:40:54,483 --> 00:40:56,007
<i>To the future!</i>

739
00:40:56,051 --> 00:40:57,541
<i>[Both chuckling]</i>

740
00:40:58,720 --> 00:41:00,654
Skumps! Skumps!

741
00:41:00,689 --> 00:41:01,951
Skumps!

742
00:41:01,990 --> 00:41:03,958
<i>A toast to this night</i>

743
00:41:03,992 --> 00:41:05,892
<i>The outlook is rosy</i>

744
00:41:05,927 --> 00:41:07,690
<i>The future is bright</i>

745
00:41:07,729 --> 00:41:09,526
<i>BO TH: Our children</i>
<i>will marry</i>

746
00:41:09,564 --> 00:41:11,361
<i>Our kingdoms unite</i>

747
00:41:11,399 --> 00:41:17,304
<i>Skumps, skumps,</i>
<i>skumps</i>

748
00:41:20,809 --> 00:41:23,403
<i>HUBERT: Ah!</i>
<i>Excellent vintage!</i>

749
00:41:23,445 --> 00:41:25,743
<i>[Hubert chuckles]</i>

750
00:41:25,780 --> 00:41:26,974
[Hiccups]

751
00:41:28,416 --> 00:41:30,907
And now, to the new home, eh?

752
00:41:30,952 --> 00:41:31,941
New home?

753
00:41:31,987 --> 00:41:33,579
Children need a nest
of their own, what?

754
00:41:33,622 --> 00:41:34,850
<i>[Hubert chuckles]</i>

755
00:41:34,890 --> 00:41:36,983
<i>A place to raise their</i>
<i>little brood, eh?</i>

756
00:41:37,025 --> 00:41:38,185
<i>[Chuckles]</i>

757
00:41:38,226 --> 00:41:40,353
<i>STEFAN: Well,</i>
<i>I suppose, in time.</i>

758
00:41:40,395 --> 00:41:42,693
<i>Of course! To the home!</i>

759
00:41:42,731 --> 00:41:44,722
-Skumps!
-Skumps!

760
00:41:44,766 --> 00:41:46,734
<i>A toast to the home</i>

761
00:41:46,768 --> 00:41:48,235
<i>One grander, by far</i>

762
00:41:48,270 --> 00:41:50,261
<i>Than a palace in Rome</i>

763
00:41:50,305 --> 00:41:52,000
Uh, let me fill up your glass.

764
00:41:52,040 --> 00:41:54,099
Ha! Ha! That last
was all foam.

765
00:41:54,142 --> 00:41:59,444
<i>Skumps, skumps, skumps</i>

766
00:41:59,481 --> 00:42:02,245
<i>[Laughter]</i>

767
00:42:03,985 --> 00:42:04,952
<i>[Hubert claps]</i>

768
00:42:04,986 --> 00:42:06,715
[String twangs]

769
00:42:06,755 --> 00:42:08,313
The plans!

770
00:42:13,195 --> 00:42:14,287
[Hiccups]

771
00:42:14,329 --> 00:42:15,728
<i>HUBERT: Weir,</i>
<i>what do you think?</i>

772
00:42:15,764 --> 00:42:17,823
Nothing elaborate, of course.

773
00:42:17,866 --> 00:42:19,993
Forty bedrooms, dining hall.

774
00:42:20,035 --> 00:42:21,730
Honeymoon cottage, really.

775
00:42:21,770 --> 00:42:22,998
You--you mean...

776
00:42:23,038 --> 00:42:25,063
you're building it already?

777
00:42:25,106 --> 00:42:26,971
Built, man! Finished!

778
00:42:27,008 --> 00:42:28,839
Lovebirds can move in tomorrow.

779
00:42:28,877 --> 00:42:30,242
Tomorrow?

780
00:42:30,278 --> 00:42:33,042
But, Hubert, they're
not even married yet!

781
00:42:33,081 --> 00:42:34,946
I'll take care of that tonight.

782
00:42:34,983 --> 00:42:36,245
To the wedding!

783
00:42:36,284 --> 00:42:37,683
Now, hold on, Hubert.

784
00:42:37,719 --> 00:42:40,017
<i>I haven't even seen</i>
<i>my daughter yet...</i>

785
00:42:40,055 --> 00:42:41,989
<i>and you're taking her</i>
<i>away from me.</i>

786
00:42:42,023 --> 00:42:43,422
<i>HUBERT: Getting</i>
<i>my Philip, aren't you?</i>

787
00:42:43,458 --> 00:42:44,686
<i>Yes, but--</i>

788
00:42:44,726 --> 00:42:46,887
<i>Want to see our</i>
<i>grandchildren, don't we?</i>

789
00:42:46,928 --> 00:42:48,088
Of course, but--

790
00:42:48,129 --> 00:42:49,653
Well, there's no time to lose.

791
00:42:49,698 --> 00:42:51,097
Getting on in years.

792
00:42:51,132 --> 00:42:52,224
Ha! Ha! Ha!

793
00:42:52,267 --> 00:42:54,098
To the wedding!

794
00:42:54,135 --> 00:42:56,160
<i>STEFAN: Now,</i>
<i>be reasonable, Hubert.</i>

795
00:42:56,204 --> 00:43:00,300
<i>After all, Aurora knows</i>
<i>nothing about all this.</i>

796
00:43:00,342 --> 00:43:02,173
-Well?
-Well, it--it...

797
00:43:02,210 --> 00:43:04,770
may come as quite a shock.

798
00:43:04,813 --> 00:43:06,007
[Sputters]

799
00:43:06,047 --> 00:43:07,241
Shock?!

800
00:43:07,282 --> 00:43:09,375
My Phillip a shock?!

801
00:43:09,417 --> 00:43:12,352
What's wrong with my Phillip?

802
00:43:12,387 --> 00:43:14,981
Nothing, Hubert.
l only meant--

803
00:43:15,023 --> 00:43:18,584
Why doesn't your daughter
like my son?

804
00:43:18,627 --> 00:43:19,753
Now, now--

805
00:43:19,794 --> 00:43:24,060
I'm not so sure my son
likes your daughter!

806
00:43:24,099 --> 00:43:25,259
Now, see here--

807
00:43:25,300 --> 00:43:27,495
I'm not so sure
my grandchildren...

808
00:43:27,535 --> 00:43:30,265
want you for a grandfather!

809
00:43:30,305 --> 00:43:33,297
Why, you--you unreasonable...

810
00:43:33,341 --> 00:43:36,333
pompous, blustering,
old windbag!

811
00:43:36,378 --> 00:43:38,141
Unreasonable? Pompous?

812
00:43:38,179 --> 00:43:39,737
En garde, sir!

813
00:43:39,781 --> 00:43:41,214
l warn you, Hubert!

814
00:43:41,249 --> 00:43:42,375
This means war!

815
00:43:42,417 --> 00:43:43,509
Forward!

816
00:43:43,551 --> 00:43:45,485
For honor! For country! For--

817
00:43:45,520 --> 00:43:47,488
[Laughing]

818
00:43:47,522 --> 00:43:49,615
[Laughing]

819
00:43:54,996 --> 00:43:56,691
What's this all about, anyway?

820
00:43:56,731 --> 00:43:58,460
Nothing, Hubert.

821
00:43:58,500 --> 00:44:00,491
Absolutely nothing.

822
00:44:00,535 --> 00:44:03,436
The children are bound
to fall in love with each other.

823
00:44:03,471 --> 00:44:04,802
Precisely.

824
00:44:04,839 --> 00:44:06,306
And as for grandchildren...

825
00:44:06,341 --> 00:44:08,571
I'll have
the royal woodcarvers...

826
00:44:08,610 --> 00:44:10,510
start work
on the cradle tomorrow!

827
00:44:10,545 --> 00:44:11,773
Splendid!

828
00:44:11,813 --> 00:44:13,508
King size, of course?

829
00:44:13,548 --> 00:44:14,515
Certainly.

830
00:44:14,549 --> 00:44:16,710
To the Woodcarver's Guild!

831
00:44:16,751 --> 00:44:19,481
<i>[Guitar notes ascending</i>
<i>and descending]</i>

832
00:44:20,989 --> 00:44:22,923
<i>[Snoring]</i>

833
00:44:24,225 --> 00:44:27,422
[Guitar notes ascending]

834
00:44:27,462 --> 00:44:30,124
[Strings twang]

835
00:44:30,165 --> 00:44:32,497
<i>MAN, DISTANTLY:</i>
<i>His Royal Highness...</i>

836
00:44:32,534 --> 00:44:34,559
<i>Prince Philip!</i>

837
00:44:34,602 --> 00:44:35,626
Phillip!

838
00:44:35,670 --> 00:44:41,209
<i>[Cheering]</i>

839
00:44:41,209 --> 00:44:43,302
Oh, Phillip!

840
00:44:43,345 --> 00:44:44,642
Phillip!

841
00:44:45,780 --> 00:44:47,907
Phillip! Hold, Phillip!

842
00:44:52,253 --> 00:44:54,118
[Panting]

843
00:44:54,155 --> 00:44:55,622
H-hurry, boy!

844
00:44:55,657 --> 00:44:58,558
Hurry! Change into
something suitable!

845
00:44:58,593 --> 00:45:00,857
Can't meet your future bride
looking like that.

846
00:45:00,895 --> 00:45:02,522
But l have met her, Father.

847
00:45:02,564 --> 00:45:04,429
You have? Where?

848
00:45:04,466 --> 00:45:05,592
Once upon a dream.

849
00:45:05,633 --> 00:45:07,191
[Phillip humming
<i>Once Upon a Dream]</i>

850
00:45:07,235 --> 00:45:09,465
HUBERT: Phillip!
Stop! Stop that!

851
00:45:09,504 --> 00:45:12,496
Phillip! P-put me down!

852
00:45:12,540 --> 00:45:15,737
Now...what's all
this dream nonsense?

853
00:45:15,777 --> 00:45:17,267
it wasn't a dream, Father.

854
00:45:17,312 --> 00:45:18,574
l really did meet her.

855
00:45:18,613 --> 00:45:19,944
The Princess Aurora?

856
00:45:19,981 --> 00:45:22,108
Good heavens!
We must tell Stefan!

857
00:45:22,150 --> 00:45:23,174
Why, this is the most--

858
00:45:23,218 --> 00:45:25,152
l didn't say it was Aurora.

859
00:45:25,186 --> 00:45:27,177
You most certainly did!
You--you said that--

860
00:45:27,222 --> 00:45:29,417
l said l met the girl
l was going to marry.

861
00:45:29,457 --> 00:45:30,947
l don't know who she was.

862
00:45:30,992 --> 00:45:32,357
A peasant girl,
l suppose--

863
00:45:32,394 --> 00:45:34,157
A peasant g-girl?

864
00:45:34,195 --> 00:45:36,220
You're--you're going
to marry a...

865
00:45:36,264 --> 00:45:38,255
[Chuckling]
Why, Phillip!

866
00:45:38,299 --> 00:45:39,596
You're joking!

867
00:45:42,637 --> 00:45:44,229
Uh...isn't he?

868
00:45:46,074 --> 00:45:49,737
No! Y-you can't
do this to me!

869
00:45:49,778 --> 00:45:52,042
Give up the throne?
The kingdom?

870
00:45:52,080 --> 00:45:54,844
For some...some nobody?

871
00:45:54,883 --> 00:45:57,374
By Harry, l won't have it!

872
00:45:57,419 --> 00:45:58,750
You're a Prince!

873
00:45:58,787 --> 00:46:01,153
And you're going
to marry a Princess!

874
00:46:01,189 --> 00:46:03,089
Now, Father, you're
living in the past.

875
00:46:03,124 --> 00:46:05,115
This is the 1<i>4</i>th century.
Nowadays--

876
00:46:05,160 --> 00:46:07,685
Nowadays,
I'm still the King!

877
00:46:07,729 --> 00:46:09,890
And l command you to come
to your senses!

878
00:46:09,931 --> 00:46:11,262
And marry the girl l love.

879
00:46:11,299 --> 00:46:12,561
-Exactly!
-Good-bye, Father.

880
00:46:12,600 --> 00:46:14,534
''Good-bye, Father.
Marry the girl you--''

881
00:46:14,569 --> 00:46:15,536
No, no!

882
00:46:15,570 --> 00:46:17,231
No, no, Phillip, stop!

883
00:46:17,272 --> 00:46:18,398
Come back!

884
00:46:18,440 --> 00:46:19,600
<i>HUBERT: Oh, Philip!</i>

885
00:46:24,979 --> 00:46:27,379
Phillip!

886
00:46:45,900 --> 00:46:47,026
Oh!

887
00:46:47,068 --> 00:46:51,266
Oh, how--how will
l ever tell Stefan?

888
00:47:37,852 --> 00:47:39,479
Whispering]
Come along, now.

889
00:47:51,466 --> 00:47:54,492
All right, in here, dear.

890
00:47:58,406 --> 00:47:59,566
[Sighs]

891
00:47:59,607 --> 00:48:01,097
<i>FLORA: Bolt the door,</i>
<i>Merryweather!</i>

892
00:48:01,142 --> 00:48:03,076
<i>Fauna, pull the drapes!</i>

893
00:48:04,145 --> 00:48:08,548
And now, dear,
if you'll just sit here.

894
00:48:08,583 --> 00:48:10,813
This one last gift...

895
00:48:10,852 --> 00:48:12,843
dear child for thee...

896
00:48:12,887 --> 00:48:16,448
the symbol of thy royalty.

897
00:48:16,491 --> 00:48:20,450
A crown to wear
in grace and beauty,

898
00:48:20,495 --> 00:48:23,726
as is thy right and royal duty.

899
00:48:26,134 --> 00:48:28,034
[Crying]

900
00:48:28,069 --> 00:48:30,367
Now, dear.

901
00:48:30,405 --> 00:48:31,565
Whispering]
Come.

902
00:48:33,274 --> 00:48:36,141
Let her have
a few moments alone.

903
00:48:37,412 --> 00:48:39,607
It's that boy she met.

904
00:48:39,647 --> 00:48:41,547
Whatever are we going to do?

905
00:48:41,582 --> 00:48:43,379
[Sobbing]

906
00:49:21,955 --> 00:49:27,325
Oh, l don't see why she has
to marry any old Prince.

907
00:49:27,361 --> 00:49:30,694
Now, that's not
for us to decide, dear.

908
00:49:42,075 --> 00:49:45,567
Maybe we should tell King Stefan
about the boy.

909
00:49:45,612 --> 00:49:47,045
Well, why don't we?

910
00:49:47,080 --> 00:49:48,274
Listen!

911
00:49:48,315 --> 00:49:51,045
Maleficent! Rose!

912
00:49:51,084 --> 00:49:52,608
ALL: Rose! Rose! Aah!

913
00:49:52,653 --> 00:49:55,178
<i>FLORA: Oh, why did</i>
<i>we leave her alone?</i>

914
00:49:55,222 --> 00:49:57,247
ALL: Rose! Rose!

915
00:50:14,875 --> 00:50:17,639
[Grunting]

916
00:50:17,678 --> 00:50:19,339
Here.

917
00:50:19,379 --> 00:50:21,040
ALL: Rose! Rose!

918
00:50:21,081 --> 00:50:23,208
Rose, where are you?

919
00:50:23,250 --> 00:50:24,842
[Echoing]
Where are you?

920
00:50:30,624 --> 00:50:34,617
[Echoing]
ALL: Rose!

921
00:50:46,373 --> 00:50:48,432
[Echoing]
ALL: Rose!

922
00:50:48,475 --> 00:50:49,772
Rose!

923
00:51:00,253 --> 00:51:02,312
ALL: Rose!

924
00:51:12,999 --> 00:51:16,730
Rose, don't touch anything!

925
00:51:16,770 --> 00:51:18,704
[Echoing]

926
00:51:18,739 --> 00:51:21,071
<i>MALEFICENT:</i>
<i>Touch the spindle.</i>

927
00:51:21,108 --> 00:51:23,167
<i>Touch it, I say!</i>

928
00:51:25,245 --> 00:51:26,940
[All gasp]

929
00:51:28,014 --> 00:51:31,575
You poor, simple fools.

930
00:51:31,618 --> 00:51:33,586
Thinking you could defeat me.

931
00:51:33,620 --> 00:51:37,112
<i>Me, the mistress</i>
<i>of all evil!</i>

932
00:51:38,191 --> 00:51:41,752
Well, here's your
precious Princess.

933
00:51:41,795 --> 00:51:43,854
<i>[Laughing evilly]</i>

934
00:51:48,535 --> 00:51:49,502
Rose!

935
00:51:49,536 --> 00:51:52,130
[Sobbing]
Oh, Rose!

936
00:51:52,172 --> 00:51:57,007
Oh, I'll never forgive myself.

937
00:51:57,043 --> 00:51:59,238
<i>FAUNA: We're all to blame!</i>

938
00:52:08,321 --> 00:52:09,811
Stefan, there's--

939
00:52:09,856 --> 00:52:12,450
there's something important
l have to tell you.

940
00:52:12,492 --> 00:52:14,619
Not now, Hubert.

941
00:52:14,661 --> 00:52:16,788
But it's about Phillip.

942
00:52:16,830 --> 00:52:17,797
Phillip?

943
00:52:17,831 --> 00:52:19,856
Oh, yes, of course, Phillip.

944
00:52:19,900 --> 00:52:21,765
Why, where is the boy?

945
00:52:21,802 --> 00:52:24,100
That's what I'm trying
to tell you.

946
00:52:24,137 --> 00:52:25,695
Well, send for him immediately!

947
00:52:25,739 --> 00:52:26,967
-But--
-Shh!

948
00:52:27,007 --> 00:52:29,635
[Fanfare]

949
00:52:29,676 --> 00:52:32,304
<i>MAN: The sun has set!</i>

950
00:52:32,345 --> 00:52:36,179
<i>Make ready to welcome</i>
<i>your Princess!</i>

951
00:52:36,216 --> 00:52:38,514
[Crowd cheers]

952
00:52:55,035 --> 00:52:56,525
[Sobbing]

953
00:53:32,339 --> 00:53:34,307
<i>[Crowd cheers]</i>

954
00:53:36,743 --> 00:53:39,769
Poor King Stefan and the Queen.

955
00:53:39,813 --> 00:53:43,305
They'll be heartbroken
when they find out.

956
00:53:45,852 --> 00:53:47,979
They're not going to.

957
00:53:48,021 --> 00:53:49,488
<i>MERRYWEATHER: They aren't?</i>

958
00:53:49,522 --> 00:53:51,285
We'll put them all to sleep...

959
00:53:51,324 --> 00:53:53,656
until Rose awakens.

960
00:54:00,500 --> 00:54:01,524
Come!

961
00:54:10,377 --> 00:54:17,715
<i>CHORUS:</i>
<i>Sleeping beauty fair</i>

962
00:54:17,751 --> 00:54:21,744
<i>Gold of sunshine</i>

963
00:54:21,788 --> 00:54:27,090
<i>In your hair</i>

964
00:54:27,127 --> 00:54:30,119
<i>Lips that shame</i>

965
00:54:30,163 --> 00:54:35,499
<i>The red, red rose</i>

966
00:54:35,535 --> 00:54:38,800
<i>Dreaming of true Love</i>

967
00:54:38,838 --> 00:54:44,777
<i>In slumber repose</i>

968
00:54:44,811 --> 00:54:53,150
<i>One day he will come</i>

969
00:54:53,186 --> 00:55:01,855
<i>Riding out of the dawn</i>

970
00:55:01,895 --> 00:55:04,887
<i>And you'll awaken</i>

971
00:55:04,931 --> 00:55:09,925
<i>To Love's first kiss</i>

972
00:55:09,970 --> 00:55:15,135
<i>TiII then,</i>
<i>Sleeping Beauty</i>

973
00:55:15,175 --> 00:55:20,010
<i>Sleep on</i>

974
00:55:20,046 --> 00:55:24,483
<i>One day you'll awaken</i>

975
00:55:24,517 --> 00:55:29,386
<i>To Love's first kiss</i>

976
00:55:29,422 --> 00:55:37,557
<i>Till then,</i>
<i>Sleeping Beauty</i>

977
00:55:37,597 --> 00:55:42,830
<i>Sleep on</i>

978
00:55:42,869 --> 00:55:45,360
[Yawns]

979
00:55:48,408 --> 00:55:51,138
[Snoring]

980
00:55:51,177 --> 00:55:54,442
Well, just been
talking to Phillip.

981
00:55:54,481 --> 00:55:57,314
Seems he's fallen in love
with some...

982
00:55:57,350 --> 00:55:59,477
[Yawns]
Peasant girl.

983
00:55:59,519 --> 00:56:01,714
Peasant girl?

984
00:56:01,755 --> 00:56:03,552
Yes? Yes?

985
00:56:05,425 --> 00:56:07,416
The peasant girl--
who is she?

986
00:56:07,460 --> 00:56:08,927
Where did he meet her?

987
00:56:08,962 --> 00:56:12,159
Just some peasant girl he met.

988
00:56:12,198 --> 00:56:13,927
Where?! Where?!

989
00:56:13,967 --> 00:56:18,370
Once upon a dream.

990
00:56:18,405 --> 00:56:20,339
Once upon a dr--

991
00:56:20,373 --> 00:56:22,364
Rose! Prince Phillip!

992
00:56:22,409 --> 00:56:23,967
Oh! Oh!

993
00:56:27,981 --> 00:56:29,243
FLORA: Come on.

994
00:56:29,282 --> 00:56:31,307
We've got to get back
to the cottage.

995
00:56:48,601 --> 00:56:51,263
Whistling
<i>Once Upon a Dream]</i>

996
00:57:18,764 --> 00:57:19,958
<i>MALEFICENT: Come in!</i>

997
00:57:25,237 --> 00:57:28,297
[Growling and snarling]

998
00:57:37,650 --> 00:57:39,140
[Cawing]

999
00:57:50,296 --> 00:57:52,491
Well...

1000
00:57:52,531 --> 00:57:55,989
this is a pleasant surprise.

1001
00:57:56,035 --> 00:57:59,801
l set my trap
for a peasant, and lo,

1002
00:57:59,838 --> 00:58:01,601
l catch a Prince!

1003
00:58:01,640 --> 00:58:05,132
[Laughing]

1004
00:58:05,177 --> 00:58:06,235
Away with him.

1005
00:58:06,278 --> 00:58:07,336
[Snarling]

1006
00:58:07,379 --> 00:58:09,040
But gently, my pets...

1007
00:58:09,081 --> 00:58:10,548
gently.

1008
00:58:11,984 --> 00:58:16,182
l have plans
for our royal guest.

1009
00:58:43,749 --> 00:58:44,841
[Gasps]

1010
00:58:48,520 --> 00:58:50,750
[Gasping]
ALL: Maleficent!

1011
00:58:50,789 --> 00:58:52,450
She's got Prince Phillip!

1012
00:58:53,592 --> 00:58:55,082
At the forbidden mountain.

1013
00:58:55,127 --> 00:58:56,424
[Gasps]

1014
00:58:56,462 --> 00:58:59,158
But we can't!
We can't go there!

1015
00:58:59,198 --> 00:59:02,565
We can, and we must!

1016
01:00:34,493 --> 01:00:35,482
[Snorts]

1017
01:00:45,037 --> 01:00:47,528
<i>[Snarling]</i>

1018
01:01:24,076 --> 01:01:26,044
What a pity Prince Phillip...

1019
01:01:26,078 --> 01:01:29,377
can't be here to enjoy
the celebration.

1020
01:01:29,414 --> 01:01:31,575
[Laughs]

1021
01:01:31,617 --> 01:01:33,551
Come.

1022
01:01:33,585 --> 01:01:36,554
We must go to the dungeon
and cheer him up.

1023
01:02:30,409 --> 01:02:32,934
Oh, come now, Prince Phillip.

1024
01:02:32,978 --> 01:02:34,946
Why so melancholy?

1025
01:02:36,114 --> 01:02:39,208
A wondrous future lies
before you.

1026
01:02:39,251 --> 01:02:42,049
You, the destined hero...

1027
01:02:42,087 --> 01:02:45,648
of a charming fairy tale
come true.

1028
01:02:50,028 --> 01:02:51,222
Behold...

1029
01:02:51,263 --> 01:02:54,027
<i>King Stefan's castle...</i>

1030
01:02:54,066 --> 01:02:56,534
<i>And in yonder</i>
<i>topmost tower...</i>

1031
01:02:56,568 --> 01:02:59,537
<i>Dreaming of her true Love...</i>

1032
01:02:59,571 --> 01:03:03,667
<i>the Princess Aurora.</i>

1033
01:03:03,709 --> 01:03:06,940
<i>But see the gracious</i>
<i>whim of fate.</i>

1034
01:03:06,979 --> 01:03:10,415
<i>Why, 'tis the selfsame</i>
<i>peasant maid...</i>

1035
01:03:10,449 --> 01:03:12,747
<i>who won the heart</i>
<i>of our noble Prince...</i>

1036
01:03:12,784 --> 01:03:14,251
<i>but yesterday.</i>

1037
01:03:17,422 --> 01:03:22,758
<i>She is indeed</i>
<i>most wondrous fair.</i>

1038
01:03:22,794 --> 01:03:25,695
<i>Gold of sunshine</i>
<i>in her hair.</i>

1039
01:03:25,731 --> 01:03:30,191
<i>Lips that shame</i>
<i>the red, red rose.</i>

1040
01:03:30,235 --> 01:03:32,669
<i>In ageless sleep...</i>

1041
01:03:32,704 --> 01:03:34,797
<i>she finds repose.</i>

1042
01:03:36,975 --> 01:03:39,409
The years roll by...

1043
01:03:39,444 --> 01:03:42,607
but a hundred years
to a steadfast heart...

1044
01:03:42,648 --> 01:03:44,582
are but a day.

1045
01:03:44,616 --> 01:03:48,416
<i>And now the gates</i>
<i>of a dungeon part...</i>

1046
01:03:48,453 --> 01:03:53,117
<i>and our Prince</i>
<i>is free to go his way.</i>

1047
01:03:53,158 --> 01:03:57,561
<i>Off he rides</i>
<i>on his noble steed...</i>

1048
01:03:57,596 --> 01:03:59,154
<i>a valiant figure...</i>

1049
01:03:59,197 --> 01:04:01,631
<i>straight and tall...</i>

1050
01:04:01,667 --> 01:04:03,828
to wake his love...

1051
01:04:03,869 --> 01:04:07,566
with love's first kiss...

1052
01:04:07,606 --> 01:04:12,771
<i>and prove that true Love</i>
<i>conquers all.</i>

1053
01:04:12,811 --> 01:04:15,746
<i>[Laughs]</i>

1054
01:04:15,781 --> 01:04:17,772
Why, you--you...

1055
01:04:22,321 --> 01:04:23,845
Come, my pet.

1056
01:04:23,889 --> 01:04:26,119
Let us leave our noble Prince...

1057
01:04:26,158 --> 01:04:28,626
with these happy thoughts.

1058
01:04:28,660 --> 01:04:29,752
[Chuckles]

1059
01:04:33,298 --> 01:04:36,290
A most gratifying day.

1060
01:04:41,173 --> 01:04:44,199
For the first time
in sixteen years...

1061
01:04:44,242 --> 01:04:46,642
l shall sleep well.

1062
01:05:03,161 --> 01:05:05,755
Shh! No time to explain.

1063
01:05:14,473 --> 01:05:16,202
Wait, Prince Phillip.

1064
01:05:16,241 --> 01:05:18,209
The road to true love
may be barred...

1065
01:05:18,243 --> 01:05:20,370
by still many more dangers...

1066
01:05:20,412 --> 01:05:23,040
<i>which you alone</i>
<i>will have to face.</i>

1067
01:05:23,081 --> 01:05:24,548
So arm thyself...

1068
01:05:24,583 --> 01:05:27,848
with this enchanted shield
of virtue...

1069
01:05:27,886 --> 01:05:31,151
<i>and this mighty sword</i>
<i>of truth.</i>

1070
01:05:31,189 --> 01:05:33,316
<i>For these weapons</i>
<i>of righteousness...</i>

1071
01:05:33,358 --> 01:05:35,258
<i>will triumph over evil.</i>

1072
01:05:35,293 --> 01:05:37,284
Now, come. We must hurry.

1073
01:05:41,700 --> 01:05:42,758
[Cawing]

1074
01:05:55,714 --> 01:05:58,182
[Yelling]

1075
01:06:11,730 --> 01:06:13,721
Whinnies]

1076
01:06:25,377 --> 01:06:26,708
FLORA: Phillip, watch out!

1077
01:06:58,510 --> 01:07:00,000
[Cawing]

1078
01:07:23,435 --> 01:07:25,665
Silence!

1079
01:07:25,704 --> 01:07:28,104
You, tell those fools to...

1080
01:07:28,140 --> 01:07:30,108
No! No!

1081
01:07:35,213 --> 01:07:37,147
FAUNA: Watch out, Phillip!

1082
01:07:45,123 --> 01:07:46,454
Hurry! Hurry, Phillip!

1083
01:07:59,804 --> 01:07:59,904
A forest of thorns
shall be his tomb.

1084
01:07:59,904 --> 01:08:03,670
A forest of thorns
shall be his tomb.

1085
01:08:03,707 --> 01:08:07,438
Born through the skies
on a fog of doom.

1086
01:08:07,478 --> 01:08:10,743
<i>Now go with the curse</i>
<i>and serve me well...</i>

1087
01:08:10,781 --> 01:08:12,772
<i>Round Stefan's castle...</i>

1088
01:08:12,816 --> 01:08:15,011
<i>Cast my spell!</i>

1089
01:08:32,569 --> 01:08:34,799
Whinnies]

1090
01:08:34,838 --> 01:08:37,932
[Laughing]

1091
01:08:49,286 --> 01:08:51,516
Whinnies]

1092
01:09:05,369 --> 01:09:07,803
No, it cannot be!

1093
01:09:11,809 --> 01:09:14,004
<i>[Samson whinnies]</i>

1094
01:09:14,044 --> 01:09:17,878
Now shall you deal
with me, o Prince...

1095
01:09:17,915 --> 01:09:22,716
and all the powers of hell!

1096
01:09:22,753 --> 01:09:25,347
[Laughing]

1097
01:09:50,414 --> 01:09:51,745
Whinnies]

1098
01:09:53,484 --> 01:09:54,974
[Roars]

1099
01:10:06,096 --> 01:10:08,064
Up! Up this way!

1100
01:10:22,946 --> 01:10:24,413
[Maleficent laughs]

1101
01:10:24,448 --> 01:10:27,212
FLORA: Now, Sword of Truth,
fly swift and sure...

1102
01:10:27,251 --> 01:10:30,846
that evil die and good endure!

1103
01:10:30,888 --> 01:10:33,152
[Screaming]

1104
01:10:56,713 --> 01:10:58,374
[Nickers]

1105
01:12:12,956 --> 01:12:16,551
Oh, oh, uh, forgive me, Hubert.

1106
01:12:16,593 --> 01:12:17,890
The wine.

1107
01:12:17,928 --> 01:12:21,193
Now, uh, you were saying?

1108
01:12:21,231 --> 01:12:23,222
Huh? l was?

1109
01:12:23,267 --> 01:12:25,360
Oh, oh, yes.

1110
01:12:25,402 --> 01:12:28,337
Well, after all, Stefan...

1111
01:12:28,372 --> 01:12:30,237
this is the 1<i>4</i>th century.

1112
01:12:30,274 --> 01:12:31,571
Yes. You, uh--

1113
01:12:31,608 --> 01:12:33,576
you said that a moment ago.

1114
01:12:33,610 --> 01:12:36,408
Well, to come right
to the point...

1115
01:12:36,446 --> 01:12:39,643
my son Phillip says
he's going to marry--

1116
01:12:39,683 --> 01:12:42,652
<i>[Trumpet fanfare]</i>

1117
01:13:05,209 --> 01:13:07,643
It's Aurora. She's here!

1118
01:13:12,416 --> 01:13:14,316
And--and--and Phillip!

1119
01:13:29,266 --> 01:13:31,894
What does this mean, boy?

1120
01:13:31,935 --> 01:13:33,459
l--l don't...

1121
01:13:37,841 --> 01:13:39,604
But, but, but...

1122
01:13:46,450 --> 01:13:48,281
l don't understand.

1123
01:14:13,677 --> 01:14:16,009
Why, Fauna,
what's the matter, dear?

1124
01:14:16,046 --> 01:14:20,608
Oh, l just love happy endings.

1125
01:14:20,651 --> 01:14:22,846
Yes. l do, too.

1126
01:14:22,886 --> 01:14:24,444
[Gasps]

1127
01:14:24,488 --> 01:14:25,648
Blue?!

1128
01:14:29,626 --> 01:14:30,957
Pink!

1129
01:14:30,994 --> 01:14:36,330
<i>CHORUS: I know you,</i>
<i>I walked with you once...</i>

1130
01:14:36,366 --> 01:14:37,355
Blue!

1131
01:14:37,401 --> 01:14:39,460
<i>...upon a dream</i>

1132
01:14:39,503 --> 01:14:42,097
<i>I know you</i>

1133
01:14:42,139 --> 01:14:44,130
<i>The gleam in your eyes</i>

1134
01:14:44,174 --> 01:14:47,473
<i>Is so familiar a gleam</i>

1135
01:14:47,511 --> 01:14:50,674
<i>And I know it's true</i>

1136
01:14:50,714 --> 01:14:55,447
<i>That visions</i>
<i>are seldom all they seem</i>

1137
01:14:55,485 --> 01:14:58,010
<i>But if I know you</i>

1138
01:14:58,055 --> 01:14:59,920
<i>I know what you'll do</i>

1139
01:14:59,956 --> 01:15:01,981
<i>You'll Love me at once</i>

1140
01:15:02,025 --> 01:15:04,425
<i>The way you did once</i>

1141
01:15:04,461 --> 01:15:06,929
<i>Upon</i>

1142
01:15:06,963 --> 01:15:08,931
<i>A</i>

1143
01:15:08,965 --> 01:15:16,531
<i>Dream</i>

